<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1325,359,825]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[264,366,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[381,589,359,384]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="areolata">
<emphasis box="[381,589,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Trapezia areolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from an unspecified number of specimens from Tahiti, Society Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[545,750,399,425]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dana" box="[766,964,399,425]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refString="Dana, J. D. (1852) Crustacea, Part I. United States Exploring Expedition, During the Years 1838, 1839, 1840, 1841, 1842, Under the Command of Charles Wilkes, U. S. N., 13 (2). C. Sherman, Philadelphia, pp. 6861618. Atlas [1855]. Vol. 14, 27 pp., pls. 1 - 96." type="book chapter" year="1852">
Dana 
<number box="[839,902,399,425]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1852.0">1852</number>
: 
<number box="[915,964,399,425]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="259.0">259</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Dana’s material is no longer extant. The species had been frequently confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Dana, 1852" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[905,1163,439,465]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septata">
<emphasis box="[905,1018,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">T. septata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dana" box="[1025,1163,439,465]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refString="Dana, J. D. (1852) Crustacea, Part I. United States Exploring Expedition, During the Years 1838, 1839, 1840, 1841, 1842, Under the Command of Charles Wilkes, U. S. N., 13 (2). C. Sherman, Philadelphia, pp. 6861618. Atlas [1855]. Vol. 14, 27 pp., pls. 1 - 96." type="book chapter" year="1852">
Dana, 
<number box="[1101,1163,439,465]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1852.0">1852</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, until 
<bibRefCitation author="Galil" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refString="Galil, B. &amp; Lewinsohn, C. (1985) On the taxonomic status of Trapezia rufopunctata (Herbst) and Trapezia flavopunctata Eydoux &amp; Souleyet (Decapoda, Brachyura). Crustaceana, 48 (2), 209 - 217." type="journal article" year="1985">
Galil &amp; Lewinsohn (
<number box="[413,474,479,505]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
showed the distinctiveness of each taxon. Considering the history of this species, a 
<typeStatus box="[433,526,519,545]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">neotype</typeStatus>
should be selected to ensure the name remains as is currently used.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1325,359,825]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
A female (MNHN­B 
<number box="[564,641,559,585]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="25313.0">25313</number>
; cl 5.3 mm, cw 6.2 mm) from Anuanuraro Atoll (
<geoCoordinate box="[1223,1320,559,585]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" precision="925" value="-20.416666">
<number box="[1223,1256,559,585]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="20.0">20</number>
º 
<number box="[1267,1299,559,585]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="25.0">25</number>
’S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[264,387,599,625]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" precision="925" value="-134.5">
<number box="[264,310,599,625]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="134.0">134</number>
º 
<number box="[320,352,599,625]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="30.0">30</number>
’W
</geoCoordinate>
), Tuamotu Archipelago, 
<collectingCountry box="[679,881,599,625]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
is herein designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[1200,1293,599,625]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dana, 1852" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[264,617,639,665]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="areolata">
<emphasis box="[264,471,639,664]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Trapezia areolata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dana" box="[478,617,639,665]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refString="Dana, J. D. (1852) Crustacea, Part I. United States Exploring Expedition, During the Years 1838, 1839, 1840, 1841, 1842, Under the Command of Charles Wilkes, U. S. N., 13 (2). C. Sherman, Philadelphia, pp. 6861618. Atlas [1855]. Vol. 14, 27 pp., pls. 1 - 96." type="book chapter" year="1852">
Dana, 
<number box="[555,617,639,665]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1852.0">1852</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It was collected by J. Poupin from 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1172,639,664]" class="Anthozoa" family="Pocilloporidae" genus="Pocillopora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1172,639,664]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Pocillopora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at a depth of 
<quantity box="[264,309,679,705]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
on 
<date box="[353,485,679,705]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1996-04">
April 
<number box="[423,485,679,705]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</date>
. The characteristic pattern on the dorsal surface of the carapace (brown lines that form a honeycomb pattern of mostly large rectangles) is visible in the 
<typeStatus box="[1230,1323,719,745]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">neotype</typeStatus>
specimen, even if out of focus and barely seen in the colour photograph of the specimen given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Castro" box="[373,545,799,825]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refString="Castro, P. (1997 b) Trapeziid crabs (Brachyura: Xanthoidea: Trapeziidae) of French Polynesia. In: Richer de Forges, B. (Ed.), Les fonds meubles des lagons de Nouvelle-Caledonie (Sedimentologie, Benthos). Etudes et Theses, 3, 109 - 139." type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="b">
Castro (
<number box="[466,529,799,825]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1997.0">1997</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 
<number box="[593,608,799,825]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
, fig. c).
</paragraph>
